items.name: De-Anime-er
items.description:
This LyCORIS removes anime from a any model and makes it photo realistic. No trigger words needed. A weight of 1 will work great for heavy anime models, you need to dial that back a bit for less anime models. It will add some realism to realistic models as well, but you need to dial it way low around 0.1 or 0.2.

It is big, or at least that's what she said, but it is doing a lot of heavy lifting. There is a lot of anime on Civitai it has to handle. I will update the details of how it was made soon in the next day or two, but for now, throw it on any anime model to make it realistic.


It has been tested and works well with these anime models:

  • MeinaMix v10.0

  • Koji v2.1

  • Flat-2D Animerge v3.0

  • Counterfeit v3.0

It does NOT seem to perform well with these:

  • AnyLoRA

  • Anything v3

In the next version, I will include better support for Anything v3 and AnyLoRA. If there are any other popular Anime models you want to make sure it supports, let me know.

items.name: Zen Aku
items.description:
This model runs nicely when it is on a weight of 1 in the prompt section. Though, for more variety, putting it at 0.85 gives that. If one is combining the looks with other models, using 0.35 to 0.5 would add a decent mix of the look to other models.

For sampling steps, I like to use 50. A set of 35 steps would give a decent look while retaining the look of the figure. Anything beyond those steps just adds more detail.

A CFG scale of 7 brings amount enough scale for the Lora. A CFG scale of 14 gives a nice dark look to the image. Beyond that, the image would start to gargle a bit. Having a scale beyond that with enough added resources gives a decayed look. A CFG scale of 10 is a nice balance between the standard and dark look.

A standard denosing strength of 0.75 is what I would suggest for images for the character output. If editing one's own pictures with the need to keep their image intact in the image to image area, then a denosing strength of 0.4 with a CFG scale of 21 is what I tend to use.

When using other resources I enjoy using the RevAnimated checkpoint more often than not. Textual Inversions like Easynegative and Deepnegative I tend to use. Badhandv4 and bad_prompt_version2-neg in the negative prompts area lessens the number of unwanted looks well from my experience.

For added fun, using Loras such as the Weregarurumon and Wolf O'Donnell by Cynfall combine well with Zen Aku since they are wolf related. The League of Legends Splash Art textual inversions by Meesh gives a nice anime look to this Lora.

items.name: GlimmerGen
items.description:
このモデルは画面の情報量を抑制しつつアニメとイラストの中間を生成する事、また男性を安定して生成する事を目的にマージしたものです。

個人的にはゲイ向けとしていますが、女性なども問題なく生成する事が出来ます。

プロンプトはdanbooruタグを使ったものを想定していますが、自然言語のみでも素直に生成できるのが特徴です。

画面の情報量を減らしたい場合、faltなどのLoRAを併用してください。

初心者にも扱いやすい素直なモデルですが、シチュエーションをプロンプトに加えないとシンプルな背景になりやすいのが欠点です。

また、男性局部の生成は不得意とする分野です。この点に関しては改修予定です。

ケモノや獣人などは確認していませんが、おそらく不得意とする分野です。プロンプトなどを練るよりも、別のモデルを採用する事をおすすめいたします。

生成にあたっての設定は以下の通りです

サンプリング：DPM++ 2M Karras
ステップ数：30
CFGスケール：5.5~7.5
Clip skip：2
NegativePrompt:badhandv4, EasyNegative or EasyNegativeV2 or verybadimagenegative_v1.3
VAE:vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.safetensors

Negativeに使われているTEは好みで選んで頂いて問題ありません。

items.name: OLD_axonometric_V1
items.description:
该LoRA模型主要是模拟轴测图画法，将室内场景进行轴测2.5d模型风格化，此LoRA最适配一些2.5d风格的模型，当然在其他像2d风格和3d写实风格也能使用（可能需要适当提高模型权重），但是如果提高权重后LoRA仍然无法生效，建议还是换一个基础大模型吧。后期我还会继续尝试优化训练过程以及训练图集的质量，制作更高质量和泛化性的LoRA模型。

The LoRA model primarily simulates the axonometric drawing technique, stylizing indoor scenes into a 2.5D model. This LoRA model is most suitable for creating models in a 2.5D style, but it can also be used for other styles like 2D and realistic 3D (although it may require adjusting the model weights accordingly). However, if increasing the weights still doesn't yield satisfactory results, it is recommended to switch to a different base model. In the future, I will continue to work on optimizing the training process and improving the quality of the training dataset to create a higher quality and more generalized LoRA model.

Base models：revAnimated_v11、chilloutmix_NiPrunedFp32Fix、deliberate_v2、OldFish_v11、anything-v4.5-pruned...

items.name: Akira Lovedoll
items.description:
Discover MY ABOUT & LINKS to find more my models and art.

Embedding of Akira real sized TPE doll created by infamous lovedoll designer @Mizuwali and distributed by PiperDoll company. For training I chose mostly close up and mostly SFW photos of Akira with dark eyes and chestnut or ash wigs. Comparing Akira with my previously made Nina embedding, I would tell that Akira looks much more like a real person.

Embedding trained for 1000 steps on 'v1-5-pruned-emaonly' checkpoint, so it should works well with most of v1.5 forks and mixes. I used dataset of 48 images with 680x680 resolution, and learning rate: "0.05:10, 0.02:20, 0.01:60, 0.005:200, 0.002:500, 0.001". Personal likeness was already reached at 20 steps!

items.description:
Update - 7/7/23 - I finally succeeded at creating a pruned version of Style 1. However, I couldn't prune it directly. I had to make an overly saturated style version 1.1 and prune that instead. It succeeded in creating a version similar to Style 1 in art style, but slightly different. While this solution worked for Style 1, it isn't working for Style 2. Therefore, I'm only making one pruned version and calling it Style 1.5.

Update - 7/7/23 - I'm having issues creating pruned versions of these particular models. I'm continuing to test new things, but every time I prune the models it destroys the art style. Hopefully, I will have pruned models for each version soon, but I may have to just leave the full versions without pruning if the issues persist.

Style 2 is out! It is a mix of Style 1 and the following Loras from Envy, all at 0.6 strength.

EnvyBeautyMix39, EnvyBeautyMix37, EnvyBeautyMix26, EnvyFantasyMix04, EnvyGoddessMix03, EnvyThiccMix01

My favorite creator on this site is Envy. I have all of his models favorited. That's why I decided I would create a mix to honor his work. This model is a blend of his Envy2DMix model and my FoolKat_Anime_Merge model.

It creates an interesting blend of the two styles for some intriguing images.

All of the images I upload for this model are unedited and don't use any special extensions like ControlNet. I do not do any inpainting or img2img to correct errors. Why? Because you deserve to see how the model works without any touchup or special extensions like ControlNet. You can surely get better images by putting in the extra work, which I do for my personal images. The samples are just meant to showcase what the model can do raw with nothing but prompt engineering.

items.name: clarity And Old Style Lora
items.description:
TuningSkin

TuningSkin 是 Reverse_v1 加上新的訓練分層融合所產生的特製 Lora，用途在於增加皮膚的特徵，同時會弱化背景表現。比較適合用在真實系列模型。這個版本強度在 0.3 ~ 0.7 之間會有比較好的效果，若超過 0.7，背景弱化會相當明顯（甚至不同），最高強度可以使用 2，你可以自己試試看。

如果你要用在漫畫風格模型，他會強烈消除色彩，你可以使用負值，但需要你自己實驗。

==================================================================

TuningSkin is a special Lora produced by Reverse_v1 with a block weight training fusion, which is used to increase the characteristics of the skin while weakening the background performance. More suitable for use in realistic series models. The strength of this version will have a better effect between 0.3 and 0.7. If it exceeds 0.7, the background weakening will be quite obvious (or even different). The highest strength can be 2, you can try it yourself.

If you are using it in a anime style models, it will strongly remove the color, you can use negative values, but you need to experiment on your own.

==================================================================

clarityAndOldStyle, Reverse

這是使用差異化更新加上 SVD 融合與部分 ESD 的方法特製 Lora，用意在於增加畫面銳利度與弱化效果（負數權重）。由於是融合實驗，所以並不保證任何效果，請自行挑選喜歡的模型測試，推薦真實系列模型。

clarityAndOldStyle 為正向 Lora，權重越高清晰度越高，反之則弱化。

clarityAndOldStyleReverse 為負向 Lora，權重越高畫面越弱化，反之則增強。

==================================================================

This is a special Lora that uses the method of differential update with SVD merged way and some ESD. It is intended to increase the sharpness of the picture and weaken the effect (negative weight). Since it is a fusion experiment, it does not guarantee any effect. Please choose your favorite model for testing and recommend real series models.

clarityAndOldStyle is positive Lora, the higher the weight, the higher the clarity, otherwise, the image will be weakened.

clarityAndOldStyleReverse is negative Lora, the higher the weight is, the weaker the image will be, and the opposite will be the clearer the image.

==================================================================

Support me on Ko-fi https://ko-fi.com/hinablue
